.IX Title "MooseX::Getopt::Meta::Attribute::Trait 3pm"
.TH MooseX::Getopt::Meta::Attribute::Trait 3pm "2013-11-30" "perl v5.18.4" "User Contributed Perl Documentation"
.\" For nroff, turn off justification.  Always turn off hyphenation; it makes
.\" way too many mistakes in technical documents.
.if n .ad l
.nh
.SH "NAME"
MooseX::Getopt::Meta::Attribute::Trait \- Optional meta attribute trait for custom option names
.SH "VERSION"
.IX Header "VERSION"
version 0.59
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 2
\&  package App;
\&  use Moose;
\&
\&  with \*(AqMooseX::Getopt\*(Aq;
\&
\&  has \*(Aqdata\*(Aq => (
\&      traits    => [ \*(AqGetopt\*(Aq ],
\&      is        => \*(Aqro\*(Aq,
\&      isa       => \*(AqStr\*(Aq,
\&      default   => \*(Aqfile.dat\*(Aq,
\&
\&      # tells MooseX::Getopt to use \-\-somedata as the
\&      # command line flag instead of the normal
\&      # autogenerated one (\-\-data)
\&      cmd_flag  => \*(Aqsomedata\*(Aq,
\&
\&      # tells MooseX::Getopt to also allow \-\-moosedata,
\&      # \-m, and \-d as aliases for this same option on
\&      # the commandline.
\&      cmd_aliases => [qw/ moosedata m d /],
\&
\&      # Or, you can use a plain scalar for a single alias:
\&      cmd_aliases => \*(Aqm\*(Aq,
\&  );
.Ve
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
This is a custom attribute metaclass trait which can be used to
specify a the specific command line flag to use instead of the
default one which MooseX::Getopt will create for you.
.SH "METHODS"
.IX Header "METHODS"
.SS "\fBcmd_flag\fP"
.IX Subsection "cmd_flag"
Changes the command-line flag to be this value, instead of the default,
which is the same as the attribute name.
.SS "\fBcmd_aliases\fP"
.IX Subsection "cmd_aliases"
Adds more aliases for this command-line flag, useful for short options
and such.
.SS "\fBhas_cmd_flag\fP"
.IX Subsection "has_cmd_flag"
.SS "\fBhas_cmd_aliases\fP"
.IX Subsection "has_cmd_aliases"
